33
00:12:57,427 --> 00:13:15,046
 Once the rice is boiled, close the lid and cook it for 10-12mts. It may vary according to the rice. At this time cook it on low flame. Do not cook it on high flame. It may get cooked fast. Stir it often.

34
00:13:17,543 --> 00:13:41,759
 Now our ghee rice is ready. Do not wait for the water to dry up. If the rice is not cooked enough, you can sprinkle some water over it and close it again. Then you will get the correct rice. Our biriyani is ready. Now we shall add the rice over the masala and cook it.

35
00:13:42,350 --> 00:13:57,232
 Add the fried onions and mix well. This will give a good taste to the biriyani masala. Mix well.

36
00:13:57,823 --> 00:14:17,399
 We are going to make the dum in this vessel itself. If you are afraid of it sticking to the bottom, you can remove the masala and add 2-3tbsp of rice over it. But if you do it the way we do it, it will not stick to the bottom.

37
00:14:18,039 --> 00:14:46,407
 Now to get a good colour and smell of the biriyani,take 2-3 tbsp of cow's milk or coconut milk. Add 1.25 tsp of turmeric powder. If you have saffron in your hand,you can add 2-3 of it to the milk. It will give a good smell and taste to the biriyani. To get a good smell to the milk,add 1 tsp of rose water.

38
00:14:46,879 --> 00:15:02,741
 It gives a special taste and smell to our biriyani. Mix well and transfer it to a plate. Add little by little while adding the rice. It doesnt look very good when you see it like this. But it will turn yellowish when the rice is done.

39
00:15:03,518 --> 00:15:22,908
